<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3527] SolrCmdDistributor drops some of the important commit attributes (maxOptimizeSegments, softCommit, expungeDeletes) when sending a commit to replicas.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3527</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Send the following command to a Solr server with many segments in a multi-shard, multi-server environment:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;curl &quot;http://localhost:8080/solr/update?optimize=true&amp;amp;waitFlush=true&amp;amp;maxSegments=6&amp;amp;distrib=false&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The local server will end up with the number of segments at 6, as requested, but all other shards in the index will be optimized with maxSegments=1, which takes far longer to complete.  All shards should be optimized to the requested value of 6.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12559868">SOLR-3527</key>
            <summary>SolrCmdDistributor drops some of the important commit attributes (maxOptimizeSegments, softCommit, expungeDeletes) when sending a commit to replicas.</summary>
